{
  "text": "Investment in power generation infrastructure and capacity is a long-term commitment that may take several decades to break even. The expected return on such investment will be determined by the discount rate, and future operating costs and revenues, all of which are uncertain. While capital costs are predictable to a good extent -even though large projects tend to be over-due and over-budget [CITATION_1] ) -future operating expenses of a power plant are mostly determined by the cost of its main fuel and the efficiency with which it uses this fuel, while total average cost depends crucially on capacity utilization and initial capital costs. 2 Future revenues, and therefore, the profit maximization strategy to be used, are determined by the regulatory-regime in place (including capacity markets in some parts of the US) and demand. In deregulated markets competition from other suppliers is also relevant.",
